<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tellemar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-26 00:49:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>In answer to a few questions<BR>
 1: The head is no drop unfortunately.  The hammer, however, isn't.  You can sell it or whatnot. It is lore, though.<BR>
 2: Yes, you must be amiable.  There are several methods to raise faction.  You can kill goblins in butcherblock, although this is slow.  You can turn in CB belts and shoulder pads to Nusbeck.  This works pretty well.  You can also free dwarven slaves in CB.  This is kinda hard to do, since you must kill the slavers for their keys, which don't always drop, and some keys don't free any slaves.  It's nice to do if you're trying to get belts in cb though.  Finally, there is a quest where you turn in runnyeye beads to Byzar himself, although i don't know the specifics of this quest, or how much exp/faction/dough you get for doing it.  <BR>
 3:Killing Trumpy is not simple.  The sragg trick is nice, but it doesn't work if you are glareing or worse with trumpy, which will happen quickly if you kill trumpy much. So eventually you'll have to wait outside the bar, because if you're glaring or worse, trumpy and his buddies will attack you, and Mr. Barstomper will kick your butt if you are involved in ANY fight in the bar.  Wait until trumpy leaves, and follow him to somewhere nice and quiet, then kick his short butt.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aaedian</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-28 12:10:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> I have done this quest several times now and to let you know the easiest way to do it follow these instructions:<BR>
<BR>
Enter the bar and walk up to trumpy.<BR>
Type the word skrag or skraggs or a similar variant 1 or 2 g's i cant remember.<BR>
<BR>
Trumpy will say "where did you hear that name" and will then<BR>
proceed to leave the bar. *** Very Important *** DO NOT ATTACK HIM WHEN HE LEAVES!!!<BR>
<BR>
Follow trumpy He will walk a fair distant to the docks, where he says something like he has to relieve himself hehe.<BR>
as soon as he says that jump him if you can root him to the spot for if corrupt guards see you they will jump you as well. And There ya go One Trumpy head on a pike pole hehe<BR>
<BR>
P.s. if you hit trumpy as he leaves the bar his buddy barstomper will cream ya hehe. Have Fun!!!!<BR>
<BR>
Aaedian<BR>
13th Season Ranger<BR>
The Band Of The Broken Bow</font></td></tr></table>
